Create a module to manage a headless tmux session for AI Workspace processes.

## New file: lib/ai/tmux-manager.ts

## Functions needed

```typescript
// Ensure the ai-workspace session exists (create if not)
async function ensureSession(): Promise<void>

// Spawn a command in a new window
// Command should include tee redirect: `claude ... | tee /tmp/ai-workspace/{id}.out`
async function spawnInWindow(
  windowName: string,
  command: string,
  cwd: string
): Promise<void>

// Check if a window exists and has a running process
async function getWindowStatus(windowName: string): Promise<{
  exists: boolean
  running: boolean  // true if process still active in window
}>

// Kill a window (stops the process)
async function killWindow(windowName: string): Promise<boolean>

// Get the output file path for a conversation
function getOutputPath(conversationId: string): string {
  return `/tmp/ai-workspace/${conversationId}.out`
}

// Read captured output (for recovery)
async function readOutput(conversationId: string): Promise<string | null>

// List all windows in session
async function listWindows(): Promise<string[]>

// Clean up output file
async function cleanupOutput(conversationId: string): Promise<void>
```

## tmux commands reference

```bash
# Create session (detached, if not exists)
tmux has-session -t ai-workspace 2>/dev/null || tmux new-session -d -s ai-workspace

# Spawn command in new window
tmux new-window -t ai-workspace -n {convId} -c {cwd} '{command}'

# Check if window exists
tmux list-windows -t ai-workspace -F '#{window_name}' | grep -q '^{convId}$'

# Check if process running in window (exit code 0 = has process)
tmux list-panes -t ai-workspace:{convId} -F '#{pane_pid}' 2>/dev/null

# Kill window
tmux kill-window -t ai-workspace:{convId}

# List all windows
tmux list-windows -t ai-workspace -F '#{window_name}'
```

## Output directory setup

```typescript
import { mkdirSync, existsSync } from 'fs'

const OUTPUT_DIR = '/tmp/ai-workspace'

function ensureOutputDir() {
  if (!existsSync(OUTPUT_DIR)) {
    mkdirSync(OUTPUT_DIR, { recursive: true })
  }
}
```

## Error handling

- tmux not installed: Throw clear error with install instructions
- Session killed externally: Recreate on next ensureSession()
- Window already exists: Kill and recreate, or return error

